The Maritime Workers Union of Nigeria (MWUN) has suspended its strike at APM Terminals in Lagos. The union took the action following the resolution of some major issues on workers’ remuneration with the port terminal operator at the weekend. Mwun President General Adewale Adeyanju said this after a meeting with the management of APM Terminals.   Appeal Court seeks support over post- 2023 elections…     UPDATED: Buhari seeks Justice Ariwoola’s confirmation…     Interstate transporters begin 25 percent fare increase Aug…   Adeyanju said the union and the terminal operator reached an agreement on resolving some of the Collective Bargaining Agreement (CBA), adding that workers will resume operational activities this week. The union leader hailed the management of the Nigerian Ports Authority (NPA) and the Executive Secretary of the Nigerian Shippers’ Council for the prompt intervention to save the nation’s economy from collapse. He reiterated MWUN’s commitment to ensuring industrial peace and harmony in the shipping industry.